Also, investigate the national dependence on that foreign company in the Nation's Education, Health and Defence fields; 


Determine the drain to the Nation's finances of the licence fees to that company; 

Recognise that the Treasury's statement  of "increasing use of Open-Source software" is unacceptable whilst in many cases, from the Department for Work and Pensions online benefits system  to the Driving Standards Agency driving theory CD-Rom, the public can only access them by using the that company's  software – and whilst this country's IT infrastructure is dependent on foreign source code to which it has no access.
